HEADWORD: Fibrocartilage
<hw>Fi`bro*car"ti*lage</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fibra</ets> a fiber + E. <ets>cartilage</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A kind of cartilage with a fibrous matrix and
approaching fibrous connective tissue in structure.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Fi`bro*car`ti*lag"i*nous</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

